==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Haphazard
<hw>Hap"haz`ard</hw> <pr>(h⟦acr⟧p"h⟦acr⟧z`⟦etil⟧rd ⟦or⟧
h⟦acr⟧p`h⟦acr⟧z"⟦etil⟧rd)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Hap</ets> +
<ets>hazard</ets>.]</ety> <def>Extra hazard; chance; accident;
random.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>We take our principles at <qex>haphazard</qex>, upon trust.</q>
<rj><qau>Locke.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>haphazard</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: haphazard
<hw>hap"haz`ard</hw> <pr>(h⟦acr⟧p"h⟦acr⟧z`⟦etil⟧rd ⟦or⟧
h⟦acr⟧p`h⟦acr⟧z"⟦etil⟧rd)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Determined by chance,
whimsy, or guesswork; unplanned; aimless; random; -- used mostly of
human actions.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Haphtarah</ent>⟦br⟧
